Item Title: The Old Plank Road on Arizona-California Highway 80
Subject: Postcards--California
Name.repository: University of California, Los Angeles. $b Library Special Collections
Relation.isPartOf: California Postcards Collection. Department of Special Collections, Charles E. Young Research Library, UCLA.
Title: The Old Plank Road on Arizona-California Highway 80
Description.note: Color photograph of wooden highway and desert scene with telephone pole and mountains in the background.
Description.caption: Decaying in the torrid sun and shifting sands, the old plank single-lane road still remains as a reminder of early day automotive travel problems through the desert sands.

Item Title: Hell's Kitchen. Mullet Isd. Salton Sea
Subject: Postcards--California
Name.repository: University of California, Los Angeles. $b Library Special Collections
Relation.isPartOf: California Postcards Collection. Department of Special Collections, Charles E. Young Research Library, UCLA.
Title: Hell's Kitchen. Mullet Isd. Salton Sea
Description.note: Photo postcard image of men sitting on benches outside of a metal-roofed shack. The shades on the outside of the structure are decorated with images of fish and birds.|~|According to Laflin, P., The Salton Sea: California's overlooked treasure. (The Periscope, Coachella Valley Historical Society, Indio, California. 1995) the structure is the Hell's Kitchen Cafe, Dance Hall and Boat Landing.
